  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Objective: To investigate the effectiveness of an online training program on medical staff in
      five public hospitals located in Sichuan, Yunnan, Hubei, and Fujian Provinces of China, on
      improving fire knowledge.

      Methods: Participants will be randomly divided into control (receiving non-fire video
      training) and intervention (receiving hospital fire video training) groups. All participants
      will complete a questionnaire of fire knowledge before and after receiving the training.

      Hypothesis: If the online training is effective, it can be promoted as a convenient and
      effective use of training and be promoted to other hospitals.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
